SIMPLE: warn
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Warn
<hw>Warn</hw> <pr>(w⟦add⟧rn)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>wernen</ets>, AS. <ets>weornan</ets>, <ets>wyrnan</ets>. Cf.
<er>Warn</er> to admonish.]</ety> <def>To refuse.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>wern</asp>, <asp>worn</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Warn</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Warn
<hw>Warn</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Warned</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Warning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>warnen</ets>,
<ets>warnien</ets>, AS. <ets>warnian</ets>, <ets>wearnian</ets>, to take
heed, to warn; akin to AS. <ets>wearn</ets> denial, refusal, OS.
<ets>warning</ets>, <ets>wernian</ets>, to refuse, OHG.
<ets>warnen</ets>, G. <ets>warnen</ets> to warn, OFries.
<ets>warna</ets>, <ets>werna</ets>, Icel. <ets>varna</ets> to refuse;
and probably to E. <ets>wary</ets>. <?/<?/<?/<?/.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To make ware or aware; to give previous information
to; to give notice to; to notify; to admonish; hence, to notify or
summon by authority; <as>as, to <ex>warn</ex> a town meeting; to
<ex>warn</ex> a tenant to quit a house.</as></def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Warned</xex> of the ensuing fight.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Cornelius the centurion . . . was <qex>warned</qex> from God by an
holy angel to send for thee.</q> <rj><qau>Acts x. 22.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Who is it that hath <qex>warned</qex> us to the walls?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To give notice to, of approaching or probable danger
or evil; to caution against anything that may prove injurious.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Juturna <xex>warns</xex> the Daunian chief of Lausus' danger,
urging swift relief.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To ward off.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Warner</ent>⟦br⟧
